						               													<description>Combat Action Command simulates a platoon, several platoons, or a force as large as a company battling another platoon or company. &amp;#10;CAC is more of a simulation than a game.&amp;#10;CAC was created as a tool for gamers, historians and the military to simulate and study small unit combat -- and to have fun. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Command a platoon up to a company&amp;#10;     Geared for 15mm, but can use 10mm, 12mm, and 20mm figures -- no rebasing&amp;#10;     Each Team stand equals one troop squad or single tank, vehicle, or gun&amp;#10;     Asymmetric turn sequence with CAC interrupt allows you to size up the situation, seize initiative, and coordinate small unit tactics&amp;#10;     Clever Data Cards for each unique Team account for training, morale, experience, and weaponry -- you spend more time commanding, not counting&amp;#10;     Includes 24 Data cards covering major US, German, and Soviet units, plus artillery, aircraft, AA, snipers, HQs, mortars, and speciality weapons like Molotov cocktails and balanced scenarios&amp;#10;     Points system for tournaments and balanced scenarios&amp;#10;     Two 1944 scenarios included: &amp;#10;         Saving Private Ryland (West Front) and &amp;#10;         Saving Field Marshall Model (East Front)&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;     Requires six-sided dice, twenty-sided dice, a scatter die, and a ruler &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
